column5: Got this neat video up at Kesagami, Water depths and colour made it difficult to get the footage I wanted, BUT we managed to score this one. Amazing how aggressive these fish are there... too bad it didn't grab the hook, but was very interesting in the white grub... So is this fish a pickeral or a walleye??
TJ, I think it's pretty easy to confirm that this is in fact an Atlantic.
Yeah and even the spot is recognizable. You should have at least 'shopped' the background.
Very cool...  Walleye are preditors  like many other species.. And when they're "active" they attack with everything they've got...
cool video ... slo mo shows definitely a short bite
yes bill confirmed as i did its an atlantic !!!!!! .....and its not stocked......hmmmm...
Should have had a stinger hook on there!
LOL.. Ive lost bigger!!!    I don t wanna catch it!!
Why am I thinking Charlie White's fishing machine??!!
Fierce attack - great footage, thanks for taking the time in setting up the video
Thanks!!  As soon as we get some weeds up at camp, ill be trying some more!!
Was thinking about Charlie White's fishing machine. as well. A favorite show back in the day.
Nice!!! To answer your question, it looks like a pickereye to me.
